WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:04,950
If shared work is growing and adoption is not, the breakdown is usually in live decisions.

00:05,000 --> 00:09,950
Volume increases quickly, but language quality improves only with explicit review loops. Teams coordinate faster when...

00:10,000 --> 00:14,950
Assign one owner, track one metric, and review one live decision every week.

00:15,000 --> 00:19,950
Use a one-week pilot to test behavior change and keep evidence from the workflow.

00:20,000 --> 00:24,950
This usually improves first-pass quality, cleaner language handoffs, and faster team adoption.

00:25,000 --> 00:29,950
Which weekly checkpoint would improve decision quality first?
